A total of 618 nasopharyngeal and anal swabs from 309 bats of 13 different species were obtained from rural areas in HKSAR (Fig. 1
, Table 1
). RT-PCR for a 440-fragment in the pol genes of coronaviruses were positive in anal swabs from 37 (12%) of 309 bats. These 37 bats were of five genera and six species, distributed over 10 of the 20 different sampling sites (Table 1). None of the nasopharyngeal swabs was positive for coronaviruses.
